
Set JAVA_HOME IN CENTOS 7
ïƒ˜ Follow the listed steps to set JAVA_HOME in CentOS 7
Log in to your server as root user.
To check your installed java version :
java -version
Set JAVA_Home Environment variable on basis of java version. For jdk-1.8.0-
openjdk .
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/java/jdk.1.8.0_60
Set JAVA_Home Environment variable on basis of java version.
export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME

It is the recommended add the following command to /etc/profile.d/.It is the
recommended place to add customizations to the system profile.
export JRE_HOME=/usr/java/jdk1.8.0_60/jre
export PATH=$PATH:$JRE_HOME/bin
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/java/jdk1.8.0_60
export JAVA_PATH=$JAVA_HOME
export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin
